+# PHASE 0235 — Patch queue ignored runtime artifacts guard — test report
+
+## Scope
+
+Patch 0235 guards the patch queue commit step against ignored runtime artifacts
+under `.var/`.
+
+## Rationale
+
+Patch 0234 validated functionally, but the automated commit step attempted to
+stage `.var/reports/eventbus_supervision_reuse_findings_triage_0229.json`.
+That path is intentionally ignored and must remain a local runtime/reporting
+artifact.
+
+## Expected behavior
+
+The patch queue may still apply patches that mention local runtime reports in
+metadata, but commit staging must exclude `.var` paths.
+
+## Authority boundary
+
+This patch does not change runtime behavior.
+
+It does not:
+
+- call `Scheduler.run()`;
+- create an EventBus;
+- control RouteProxy or ControlProxy;
+- mutate SHM;
+- decide policy;
+- write SQL or Qdrant;
+- call GitHub;
+- add non-stdlib dependencies.
+
+## Validation
+
+- `git apply --check`: OK on a control tree.
+- `compileall tests`: OK on a control tree.
+- targeted rule test: OK on a control tree.
