+# Patch queue ignored runtime artifacts guard — 0235
+
+## Decision
+
+Patch queue commits must not stage ignored runtime artifacts under `.var/`.
+
+`.var/` is a local runtime/reporting area. It may contain audit outputs,
+triage reports, smoke outputs, replay files, and generated local diagnostics.
+Those files are useful during development, but they are not source artifacts and
+must not be part of the committed patch payload.
+
+## Trigger
+
+After the all-surfaces passive supervisor smoke passed, the automated commit
+step attempted to stage:
+
+```text
+.var/reports/eventbus_supervision_reuse_findings_triage_0229.json
+```
+
+Git correctly rejected it because `.var/` is ignored.
+
+## Canonical behavior
+
+Patch queue application may use local reports for validation, but commit staging
+must filter `.var` paths before invoking `git add`.
+
+```text
+patch metadata / changed files
+  -> filter ignored local runtime artifacts
+  -> git add source/docs/tests/tools only
+```
+
+## Boundary
+
+This is a patch-queue hygiene guard, not a runtime feature.
+
+It does not:
+
+- create or replace the EventBus;
+- change scheduler orchestration;
+- call or wrap `Scheduler.run()`;
+- control RouteProxy or ControlProxy;
+- mutate SHM;
+- decide policy;
+- read or write SQL/Qdrant;
+- call GitHub;
+- introduce VisPy;
+- add non-stdlib dependencies.
+
+## Relation to supervision work
+
+The passive supervision path remains:
+
+```text
+EventBus -> PassiveSupervisorSink -> CellularState -> snapshot/audit optional
+```
+
+Patch 0235 only prevents local `.var` evidence from breaking the commit step.
