+# Code rule — 0235 patch queue ignored runtime artifacts guard
+
+## Rule
+
+Patch queue commits must not stage `.var/` runtime artifacts.
+
+`.var/` is reserved for local runtime outputs, reports, audit files, replay
+fixtures, smoke outputs, and developer diagnostics. These files may inform a
+patch, but they must not be committed by the patch queue.
+
+## Required behavior
+
+Before `git add`, the patch queue commit step must exclude:
+
+```text
+.var
+.var/*
+```
+
+## Forbidden behavior
+
+The patch queue must not require `git add -f .var/...` for normal patches.
+
+## Runtime boundary
+
+This rule does not authorize any runtime behavior.
+
+It explicitly does not authorize:
+
+- Scheduler execution;
+- proxy control;
+- SHM mutation;
+- policy decisions;
+- SQL/Qdrant writes;
+- GitHub mutation;
+- a new EventBus;
+- VisPy runtime integration.
